cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MA, cs.GT

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on analyzing the age of information in wireless networks, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture.
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the characterization of timeliness in wireless networks, which is related to information theory.
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper studies the effect of deadline constraint on the age of information, which is related to control systems.
4. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The paper considers a Poisson bipolar network, which can be modeled as a multiagent system.
5. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The paper derives upper and lower bounds for the cumulative distribution function of the average age, which involves game-theoretic concepts.
